    <item>
      <title>SOBS: Sudden Onset Boyliking Syndrome</title>
      <author> The_Luce </author>
      <link>https://www.scribblehub.com/series/1340277/sobs-sudden-onset-boyliking-syndrome/</link>
      <comments>https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1340277-sobs-sudden-onset-boyliking-syndrome/chapter/1340283/#comments</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">fa01fbda275fbcdc57b95de1e3bbe4de2099dd39</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 11 Dec 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Two weeks after realizing she's a girl - through a convoluted series of hijinks - Alice visits her best friend with a brand new problem - she suddenly, and very inexplicably, finds herself attracted to guys! There's only one explanation on what could be behind this, and it's just like in the stories she'd always read: Sudden Onset Boyliking Syndrome!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1340277-sobs-sudden-onset-boyliking-syndrome/chapter/1340283/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;SOBS: Sudden Onset Boyliking Syndrome&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;div class="wi_authornotes"&gt; &lt;div&gt; &lt;div class="p-avatar-wrap"&gt;&lt;a class="avatar has-link" href="/profile/135183/the_luce/"&gt;&lt;img id="acc_ava_change profile" alt="" src="https://cdn.scribblehub.com/avatar/s/33/ava_135183_1727076877.jpg"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="an_username"&gt;&lt;a href="/profile/135183/the_luce/"&gt;The_Luce&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div style="clear: both;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="wi_authornotes_body"&gt; Another year, another silly little story making fun of old genre tropes. All is not what it seems!&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Jenna, I think I'm down with a case of... the SOBS!"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"What?" I asked, groggily rubbing sleep from the corners of my eyes. What the heck had Alice woken me up at 5:00 in the morning for? Glancing at her face, it didn't look like she was crying, so... I had no idea what she was talking about.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Um... let me start at the beginning," she said, letting herself into the house. She was lucky my parents were away; I doubted they'd be happy to have someone knocking at the door this early. "So, you know how I realized I was trans a couple weeks ago?"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Yeah?" I raised an eyebrow. How could I forget? She had went from an average-looking, if awkward, guy to a total girly girl in the span of a long weekend... and she said it was an accident! Something about a beach resort, forgotten luggage, and an evil cousin? I dunno, I wasn't there.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She peered at me ominously, like she was about to start telling some scary ghost story, "Well, ever since then... I've been feeling weird."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Weird... how?" I asked, shutting the door.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Alice blushed, which very much betrayed the spooky tone she had been going for. I had a sinking feeling that I knew where this was going. She seemed reticent to offer anything more, despite being the one to come to me for whatever advice she needed.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Sighing, I dragged her upstairs to my room, something which had also caused her to blush in years past. I always figured she was just embarrassed about being in a girl's room, but... looking back, maybe she was envious.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She smoothed out her dress beneath her and daintily sat at my desk chair. As per usual - the new usual, anyway - she had a full face of makeup and not a hair out of place. I had no idea how she did it, especially at a time like this, when nobody should even be awake.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Yawning, I was once again reminded of how little sleep I had gotten. Damn it, girl, it was a Saturday. Saturday is specifically&lt;em&gt; for&lt;/em&gt; sleeping! Sitting down on my bed, I questioned her, "So? What is it?"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She blushed even redder at my pressing, but managed to speak up, "Um- um- um... so, a few days ago some guys were saying mean things about me at lunch, and they wouldn't leave me alone..."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Seriously?" I scowled, "Ugh, those transphobic a-"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She waved her hands in front of herself, cutting me off, "No, it's okay, 'cause..." she, somehow, turned a deeper shade of red, and began smiling dreamily, "Well, Nick saved me. He was all like 'begone, foul scum!' and they were like 'wah!' and ran away, 'cause he's cool as heck and knows jujutsu."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ah... I knew it. I'd always kinda suspected her and Nick had &lt;em&gt;something&lt;/em&gt; going on between them. Her crush must've been multiplied tenfold by everything that had happened recently... As far as I was aware, though, Nick had never been a chuuni. She probably embellished her story a bit. "So, uh, how do you feel about that?"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She tilted her head, "How I feel? Isn't it obvious? I'm down with the SOBS!"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"&lt;em&gt;What&lt;/em&gt;?"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Oh! Sorry, I didn't explain the acronym," she giggled, "I call it SOBS: Sudden Onset Boyliking Syndrome. It's like in all the stories I read!"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;...What the hell was she talking about? What stories was she reading? &lt;em&gt;Sudden Onset Boyliking Syndrome&lt;/em&gt;? "Uh..." I blinked, "Can you explain, like, any of that?"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She put her finger to her chin thoughtfully, biting her lip, "Gosh, this is almost as embarrassing as when my parents found out I was hiding my gynecomastia. Um, basically, I suddenly like-"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Gynecomastia?! Since when?!" I blurted. Alice did&lt;em&gt; not&lt;/em&gt; have any boobs before, that was for sure. I figured her new bras were just padded! Maybe she meant, like, a mild case in the past that went away.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Eep!" Her eyes widened as she realized what she said. "Yeah, they've been growing for, um, a year or... two..." She poked her pointer fingers together, looking incredibly meek as she continued, "I was covering them up with a binder, 'cause I didn't want anyone to know... but then, y'know, &lt;em&gt;everything&lt;/em&gt; happened."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This girl... I didn't even know what to say to her, about any of that. I'd always known there was something off with her, like she was keeping some big secret, but as of recent events I had thought it was just the trans thing! "Wh- why didn't you see a doctor about them? Why was it happening?" I gasped, "Were you secretly taking hormones?"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Nope!" she replied with a shy grin, "Apparently I just naturally have high E and low T levels! Lucky, right? No wonder my voice never got that deep."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Yeah..." I mumbled, thinking back to my interactions with her in the past. Maybe she always was kinda effeminate. Like how the guys made fun of her for shaving her body hair. She always said it was for swimming, but I had literally never seen her go swimming. Certainly not in the middle of winter.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I always thought it was kinda cute how she wasn't like the other guys, but I supposed, now, it was plainly obvious why.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Anyway! Sorry, you distracted me," she giggled, before looking embarrassed again, "So... what I was saying before... I... I really like boys now! Out of nowhere!"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Really? So she had nothing going on with Nick, before? Huh. That was kind of a relief, actually. Here she was, though, suddenly saying she likes guys now. I tilted my head back and forth, debating whether to ask her something, before finally going for it, "Do you? I mean, maybe you just really liked being treated like a girl."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Hmm..." she thought about it, getting up from the chair to sit next to me on the bed, snatching up one of my stuffed animals. She turned to look me in the eyes. What was she doing? Did she... did she want to try kissing me?!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Nope!" she finally spoke up. Did I say that out loud or something? "Like, when Nick saved me, I looked over at him to thank him, and he was so handsome. I jumped right into his arms, and woah, I never noticed how nice boysmell was before!"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Oh," I replied, averting my eyes, "That's weird. I don't think sexuality can just change like that."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"You'd think so, but it's actually exactly like in all my favourite stories! You know, like, when a guy becomes a girl, and then she falls for her guy best friend. Or the star quarterback. It happens all the time. Well, except for in the lesbian stories, but I don't like those ones as much."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This was far from the first time I had no idea what she was talking about - she had a habit of assuming her conversation partner always knew exactly what she was referring to - but this was by far the most bewildering. What the heck were these stories?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Wait, so you really had no interest in him before?" I somehow doubted this.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Nope! None at all. He was just, like, y'know, my best friend. Sure, maybe I thought about what it'd be like to be his girlfriend sometimes, but that doesn't really count, 'cause..." she trailed off, squirming a little as her face turned red once again, "Well, anyway, it definitely wasn't what I feel now when I look at him! Now, it's like... holy crap!"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"What do you mean?" Honestly, I couldn't relate to her experiences with this at all. No guy had ever made me feel anything close to that. Except for maybe... well, that doesn't count anymore.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Well, it's just... I see him now, and I get all giddy, and my knees start wobbling, and I stutter through all our conversations! Nobody's ever made me feel like that, not even the girls I used to have crushes on when I was a boy."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Huh?" I perked up, curious what kind of girls Alice liked... or rather, used to like. Apparently.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She shrugged, "Like... when I had a crush on a girl, it was sort of a longing feeling? Like, gosh she's so pretty, and her skin's so nice and clear, and I really like her outfit... stuff like that. They always made me kinda bummed, 'cause I'd never have that."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I blinked, "Are you sure that's not just... envy?"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Hmm, maybe. I get that feeling way less now, and that might be because I &lt;em&gt;didn't&lt;/em&gt; never have that," she mused, flopping onto her back, plushie hugged tightly in her arms.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;An idea popped into my head. "Hey, Alice, I have a thought experiment for you."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She perked right back up, "Ooh, I love thought experiments. Like, I always &lt;em&gt;thought&lt;/em&gt; about &lt;em&gt;experimenting&lt;/em&gt;."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"With what?"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"My gender, duh." She stuck out her tongue. Rude.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I rolled my eyes and sighed at her antics, "Anyway... like, how do you feel when you imagine being together with Nick? Like, going on dates and kissing and stuff."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She winked at me when I said 'stuff', and then immediately turned red. That dork. "Um! Um...! It feels... really nice. I get all squirmy and happy. See, I really like boys now!"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Sure... but now imagine doing all those things, but you're still the boy you used to be."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The cute, blushy squirming she had been delightedly engaging in a moment ago faded to an uncomfortable grimace. I almost felt bad for it, but she needed to understand what I was thinking.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She frowned, "I dunno, that doesn't do anything for me. Kinda grosses me out, actually... Wait, does that make me homophobic? I don't wanna be homophobic!"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I placed my hand on her shoulder to calm her down, "Don't worry, Alice. That doesn't make you homophobic, it just makes it more obvious what's going on here."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Why? I'm &lt;em&gt;pretty&lt;/em&gt; sure it's the SOBS thing. I mean, even now, it's messed with my mind so much I'm not even into girls when I think back to when I was a guy," she mumbled, twiddling her thumbs as she looked down at her lap. She jerked her head back up and gasped, "Actually, wait...!"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Huh? Did you figure something out?"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She stared at me wide-eyed in horror, "I just realized... if this is like the stories..."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Yeah...?" What absurd idea was she going to come up with next? I was morbidly curious.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"That means... you're my girl bestie with whom I have romantic tension but then leave near the end because of my overwhelming, sudden attraction to boys! Oh gosh, you're not gonna try to kiss me, are you? I've always seen you as more of a sister!" she appeared distraught - almost getting a real case of the sobs - even as she spewed nonsense. 'Whom'?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ouch. That last line really hurt. Other than that, though... "Alice, life isn't like a story. I dunno &lt;em&gt;what&lt;/em&gt; you're reading," it sounded rather awful, and heteronormative, "but people don't just have, like, pre-defined roles to fill. Be your own person. If you like guys, then you like guys. You don't have to attribute it to some... made-up condition."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"It's not-" she earnestly spoke up.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I gave her a pointed look. "Here's an idea," I said.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"What? Got some proof that SOBS isn't real?"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Not &lt;em&gt;exactly&lt;/em&gt;... but do you wanna take a bet?" I asked, holding up my phone.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;***&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Uh, yeah. I always thought you had a crush on me for years. Sorry I never said anything about it, though. I figured you wouldn't wanna deal with the embarrassment, 'cause I'm straight. Huh... I guess that's not a problem, now," Nick confirmed my hypothesis, looking confused as to why I held this meeting.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Alice swore under her breath, because she owed me five bucks and was also owned by facts and logic.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I beamed, holding a hand out. She placed the bill in my hand. "What do you say now, Alice?"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She sighed, monotonously replying, "You were right. SOBS isn't a real condition. I &lt;em&gt;guess&lt;/em&gt; I liked boys the whole time."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Yup," I smugly confirmed, then added with a wink, "So, what are you gonna do with that information? Think about what Nick said."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Nick, meanwhile, stood there like a dope. He had no idea what was going on, as usual. I never really understood the appeal of guys, they were all so annoying and unaware. I supposed he had his upsides, though, like defending Alice against transphobes.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Alice took a few words to process what I said, and then her eyes turned to saucers. She tackle-hugged Nick to the ground, which I thought was assuming too far ahead. Nick didn't seem to mind, even as she confessed her love to him.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Then it got disgusting when they started &lt;em&gt;kissing&lt;/em&gt;. They got really into it. Yuck, I couldn't stand the sight of Alice kissing some dumb boy. She deserved way better than that.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Weird. Did I suddenly become a lesbian, or something?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div class="wi_authornotes"&gt; &lt;div&gt; &lt;div class="p-avatar-wrap"&gt;&lt;a class="avatar has-link" href="/profile/135183/the_luce/"&gt;&lt;img id="acc_ava_change profile" alt="" src="https://cdn.scribblehub.com/avatar/s/33/ava_135183_1727076877.jpg"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="an_username"&gt;&lt;a href="/profile/135183/the_luce/"&gt;The_Luce&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div style="clear: both;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="wi_authornotes_body"&gt; Thanks for reading! If you liked this story, consider commenting, or checking out my other stuff. Or something. :P&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
