      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;When the overly cheerful but ill Sorceres Alcazaar set out to journey through the land of Deos Graças she wasn't expecting to be accompanied by the duelist Fascinaru. Together they cross the land and do as Sorcerers do, help those that they come across and experience the world, perhaps for the last time. The destination is the Council of Miraennas and in between their departure and their arrival anything can happen.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;From a blossoming romance to a world-changing duel.&lt;br /&gt; Such is the Intricate Art of Assassination.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1336583-the-intricate-art-of-assassination/chapter/1336595/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;Prologue initial part. The Son, the Holy Seer and the Gods.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The gods are a part of every aspect of creation. Even its end.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;We, mortal beings, shaped them as they are by the sheer devotion of our faith, and in return, they shape the world to fit us better. Such is the gift of the gods. From the conception of existence to the creation of the great furnace and the wheel.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;To the end of every single living thing.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;We are truly blessed by the gods, unlike the Humans and their disgusting simulacrum of a deity.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Like always temples bring in the fervor of faith to the forefront of my mind.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Once again I find myself in the hall of the gods, the temple of Fascination. Seat of her Holiness the Holy Seer, holy mother of the Dark Elves.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;My assailant.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;What part of me will I leave behind today?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The first time I came I left my innocence behind.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The last time I came here I left my beloved sword Fantasma.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;How did this holy place came to be infested with this foul woman? It’s said that the temple’s high walls and equally tall windows was built by the gods themselves when they were still recently born. When they were still fledgling beings.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I always wondered if that was true.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;A part of me is saying that it was a lie, another is telling me that it’s all true.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;No time for such thoughts as I approach her.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;High walls, tall windows, thuribles, and silk carpets all over covering the temple’s stone.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Right at the center of it all is the holy seer on her throne surrounded by the holy maidens that serve her, each of them having lived an untold number of years, my existence the same as them blinking to me.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;What is three centuries compared to five millennia?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;What is five millennia compared to being there at the creation of all things?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;How can I not kneel in the prescience of the Holy Seer?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Your Holiness. Your adopted son is here.” And I detest it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“How many years has it been my son?” Not long enough.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Sixty-five.” So close to one hundred.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I hate the sound of her voice, I hate the way this temple smells, I hate the way her existence stains the faith I have in the gods. “You’ve been away for far too long and yet you have changed so little. I longed for you my son.” Of course you did.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; Is it normal for a mother to long for their child? Yes. Not like this, not like this.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;One of your maidens tells me to rise and approach you, which I do without hesitation as you taught me so many years ago, and I hide my contempt as I approach because you’ve taught me to be scared of you. I am not strong enough to throw you down but I am strong enough to hide my plans from you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Your touch disgusts me, the way your skin feels on mine, the way you look at me, the way you breathe, your smell, everything about you is detestable.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Perhaps this is the gods way to test me? Put me in front of someone so utterly detestable and see how I react? Will my self-control reward me?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Yes, but you don’t know that yet.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; I dare hope so, I doubt it will happen. “Your hair. It’s long.” And you tug on it hard, and again, and again till a few strands leave in your hands. “Cut it.” You say.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;“Right now your Holiness? I believe we have better things to do now don’t we?” Of course we do, she doesn’t care.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Cut it.” And one of your whores gives me a knife.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I spent the last fifty years growing my hair, something I took a lot of pleasure in doing. Silver like the moon, great in a braid, specially if I put flowers on it. Or in one case a few ornaments that long gone child gave to me. It was reaching to the back of my tights even. A pain to take care off but nothing that is worthwhile is easy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;How many nights have been spent with others admiring it, passing their fingers through my locks, enjoying its smell? How many times have I found myself playing with it?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;It took me fifty years to grow my hair, it took me five minutes for me to cut it. Now my locks are on the floor, dead and abandoned. “Better. A man of your stature should look the part. Do not disobey me so again.” You say licking your lips. I know what you are thinking about you animal.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;You aren’t better than a Human, both of you are animals driven by simple instincts.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Sex, violence, manipulation. Again and again.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;And so I will defy you and everything you believe in.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I will, again and again.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;You’ve grown quiet, because you are done tormenting me? No, I would be too lucky for that. “I heard stories, of someone that is in our order, and yet I have never met, nor trained. Someone who’s been getting a reputation as both a bodyguard and a duelist. A so-called dark Elf by the name of Fascinaru. Have you heard of her?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I can’t say I have your Holiness. But I can assure you, stories never match reality, we both know that.” In the stories you are a kind and merciful woman, in reality, you are simply an animal.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Perhaps.” And you grow quiet but not for long, never for long. “Even so, you need to be ready to face this Fascinaru” You know more than what you are letting on, don’t you? “I can see it, yes. Eventually, you and her will come into conflict. Yes.” Interesting. “I’m sure it won’t be long until that day.” I know how your visions work, you never tell everything you saw. What are you hiding from me?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Consider this a permanent objective till I say otherwise.” I nod. There is more then.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;You don’t waste time. “We came to know of a human sorcerer that will be traveling to the Council of Miraennas soon, with her will be what we believe to be a class nine Grimmoire.” Impossible. Class nine? Of the ten classes of danger for a Grimmoire to get a class nine so suddenly? “Her master is in need of a blade for hire to protect her, so it will be easy to find them I’m sure.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I can handle it. “Your job is to find and follow them, and learn what this Grimmoire holds.” Then she’s sure this isn’t a class nine. Had this be one she would be demanding the immediate destruction of it, no reading necessary, something is afoot.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“This mission is of utmost importance, my son.” You are not my mother. You are my assailant. “We need to know the contents of that Grimmoire, to be sure if they contain anything that could risk breaking the seal or even summoning the powers of the Ill God. If you find evidence that it does then you are to eliminate the sorcerer immediately and make sure that the Grimmoire is destroyed.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“What if there’s no evidence of that?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Then follow the sorcerer to the council and once you can enter in contact with us do so.” One of the maidens approaches me with a small stone in her hand. “You will be given this seal, write your report to me in a letter and use this wax seal to mark it, tell the maiden that the message is of utmost importance and must be given to me as soon as possible.” The seal of the seer, no one can look at the contents of any letter containing it. Only she can. “Once I receive the letter I will send an agent to contact you.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I assume I’ll have to keep following the target if that’s the case?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yes. We will find you son, worry not for that.” It’s been too long since I had the vain hope of escaping your grasp, I know you will find me. “Either way, you will be given new orders so be prepared. This mission will be long and difficult.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;You are planning something, aren’t you? Why would you need me to follow a class nine Grimmoire? Protocol says that such a tome needs to be destroyed immediately, suspicion or not. So why simply follow the target?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;If I were her I would use this opportunity to attack the Council of Miraennas then. And perhaps this is the plan?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;But why tell me to follow the Grimmoire?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You are now dismissed.”&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;There’s something in that tome that you want, isn’t there?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Thank you, your Holiness.” I kneel once again, her hand on my head as she blesses me. Once I’m up I turn around and leave.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I can never run away from here, such would be unbecoming.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;That Grimmoire. I need to find it, whether it has the runes of the Ill God or not I need to destroy it.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Once done I will think of what to do next.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;What is the Holy Seer’s plan?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The steps outside of the temple have always been a place of both comfort and disgust for me.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Comfort because now I am free of the Holy Seer’s presence.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Disgust because I know I will be here again in her presence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;There’s little comfort in this life of mine.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I already miss how long my hair used to be.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;What will I lose next time I come?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
