      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Now officially within their relationship, Falke finds something inescapable about herself holding her back from what her heart yearns for.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;(This is a sequel to The Dreamers Wake.)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1332653-but-my-mind-holds-the-key/chapter/1332655/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;God Lives&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Falke sat on the couch with a novel, trying to keep her eyes on the unfolding storyline before her and not have them wandering off to the bedroom door just around the corner. She couldn’t hear them, not all the time, but she could feel them constantly, could almost picture the sweet-talking, kissing, biting, and thrusting in her head. She lowered her eyes to the book and turned a page, but a sudden jolt rippled through her torso and arms, making her shake the book, and what followed after was the quiet, but unmistakable growl of a low-pitched moan. Whether it had come from Elster or Ariane, she couldn’t tell, but Falke had felt it before she had heard it. She sighed- this had been going on for over an hour and a half.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She closed her book with a grumble and looked around the living room she sat in: the rows of books and movies on shelves were absent, save for a couple sitting by themselves next to the television; the paintings which once sat on the walls were removed and all sat in a stack on the side of the room with many towers of cardboard boxes accompanying them. Elster had finally managed to find a bigger apartment for the three while they still tried for more, and thanks to a little behind-the-scenes ‘encouragement’ from Falke, the apartment supervisor offered it to them at an extremely competitive rate. She knew Elster and Ariane tried to avoid altering their new reality as much as possible, to maintain a feeling of realness and not blind fantasy, but Falke was always willing to bend the rules a little just for them.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Because they deserved it.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;They would be moving at the end of the season, but until then, it was business as usual, and for Elster and Ariane, there was a lot of business to be had.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke felt another reverberation coming from the bedroom and tensed up just as the whisper reached her ears.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;A plentiful amount of business, indeed.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane joked to her while Elster was out of earshot that they wanted to ‘make the most of the mattress’ before they left for their new place, but so far it seemed as though they were just excited about moving to an apartment where they would have room for their eventual family, and that excitement led to other forms of excitement.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;And Falke was excited too, even as she tried to hide and bottle it.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster and Ariane had noticed. They had invited her to join them on more than one occasion, and she already regularly slept through the night with them both, but joining them in that way-&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She didn’t feel she was ready.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;But she wanted to be.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke closed her eyes and breathed deeply in and out. Replika were not programmed to feel these kinds of physical desires, let alone feelings like love and yearning, and she was woefully under-equipped to deal with them herself. But damn it if she didn’t try.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Her forehead crystals softly glowed as she constructed a space for her to feel the things she wanted so badly. A Gestalt body modeled after her biosynthetic one: commandingly tall, thin, lithe, limbs graceful as a dancer’s. She laid her simulacra atop a pillowy bed and tried to pleasure herself. She rubbed up and down every part of her that ached for touch, ran her fingers up and down a body that begged for intimacy, and even found herself with her hands clenched around her neck, fighting for control over a body that she created but was not hers.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;It wasn’t enough; all she could do was wish they were another’s hands.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Still, it was a good start, but as she tried to bring Elster and Ariane into her space to complete her desire she kept messing up details about them. Their faces were blank, hands too small or too large, and bodies sometimes twisted or deformed.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;They weren’t real like the women in the room just next to her, and no matter how hard she tried, her mind rejected her built fantasy.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke opened her eyes to the sound of a door opening, but only stared blankly at the now blank television across from her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“...Falke, are you alright?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster’s voice finally reached her and she blinked rapidly. “I am fine, yes, yes,” she said, having to turn her head in multiple directions before she found which angle Elster looked at her from. Her hair was very frazzled and messy, and her eyes a bit dulled from exhaustion, but what immediately jumped out the most to Falke was that she only wore a pair of loose pyjama bottoms. This left her completely topless, presenting a veritable cornucopia of a body that begged for her attention; she fought against the urge to not be seen staring at her well-defined rows of abdominal muscles glistening with a light sheen of sweat, her thick, corded arms as she stretched her equally fierce shoulders, or her round, full, endlessly squeezable breasts, adorned with her perky, firm nipples.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke was born with the essence of godhood instilled in her, an attitude that was only encouraged and enforced by the dozens of controllers and Protektors who served directly under her, but to Falke, the very fact that a perfectly chiselled being in both mind and body such as Elster before her wasn’t being actively worshipped felt profane to her, and she begged herself to be allowed to be the one to do so.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster scratched the back of her head and frowned as she fought back a yawn. “I had to call out to you three times before you answered. Are you sure you’re okay?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke quickly put a hand up to her lips as she feigned a light cough, but it still took her a while to answer Elster again, she was too preoccupied by new sounds coming from the bathroom next to the bedroom: a running faucet, and someone who could only be Ariane gargling water, followed by a heavy spit. She did this thrice before she finally exited the bathroom for the bedroom again, during which Falke took in a slow breath and exhaled quickly, trying to compartmentalize and push aside the mental image screaming into her head from the knowledge of what Ariane must have been doing in bed with Elster. However, as Ariane left the bathroom, she briefly saw Falke and Elster in the living room and silently waved at them, meaning Falke also saw her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane’s hair was also a mess, showing frazzles in every direction, but her eyes and smile carried an energy of yearning for more, made even more apparent when she blew Elster a playful kiss. But yet again, what caught Falke’s attention the most was what Ariane was wearing, or rather, what she wasn’t. She had on only her semi-transparent nightgown, which months ago would not have even batted an eye, but it was a small piece of lingerie meant for a small body, and wonderful, peaceful domesticity had certainly caught up to the snow-haired woman. It certainly helped that her new partner Falke was more than willing to cook for her and Elster any amount and frequency of gourmet meals she was born with the knowledge of.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke only saw Ariane for a couple of seconds before she dipped back into the bedroom, but that was enough to see that the hem of the nightgown which had once gone comfortably below her buttocks now sat almost right in the centre line of her h