      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Layla unwittingly discovers an alien scout on her apartment's roof during her Friday night smoke session.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1327809-synaptic-eclipse/chapter/1327813/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;1 &amp;#8211; Layla&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;Fridays are for letting loose. That's my mantra as I lay on the couch. Brew on the side table (a repurposed moving box), anime reruns I've already seen playing at my desk. My thoughts jumble as the weed sinks in.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;Tired from work, no one to talk to, drugs are my temporary escape. The second shift premium hardly keeps me running week to week. Thankfully weed is legal here, cheap too.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;Letting my high control my mood, I drift by the difficult and the painful. Avoiding harsher thoughts, I try to let myself mellow out. Looking out my window at the night sky, stars dulled by the city lights, the waning moon still shining, somehow. My mind can't help but dance at the surface of the dark side.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;My job sucks, don't wanna think about that. Pay could be better too, at least I've got this apartment. Friends all moved for work or are on different shifts, hardly any company these days. No need to dwell on that now, I've already spent too much time down and ruminating about it. Looking at my desk, I eye the stylus. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;Maybe art can get me out&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;, I think, more pessimistic than not.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;I get up and draw for a bit. Dumb little doodles. Idly drawing the moon in negative.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;I wonder if I'm stuck. No way out, trapped in an eternal loop of jobs that I can stand just a bit more than the last. Maybe I'll miss some steps and have to try hard for improvement. Maybe there's a ceiling? I don't know. I banish the subject.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;It's Friday after all, late at night. I let loose like I should. Like I need. I zone out. Turn the anime down. Doom scroll for a bit and then shitpost in servers full of friends I don't get to see anymore. Take a bleary nap and then masturbate to the thought of affection. A couple hours pass.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;Taking advantage of a spark of productivity, I start to tidy my apartment back up. Some dishes get put in the dishwasher. Put some errant trash in the bin. I pour out my bong water and rinse out my piece. Satisfied with my work, I get a tinge of disappointment as I feel myself starting to come down.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;Fridays are for letting loose, right?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt; I think to myself, eyeing the clock on the microwave.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;1AM, it screams into my irises. I figure that I probably shouldn't smoke anymore tonight, then I wipe the moisture out of my bowl, and pack another. Not wanting to miss my fade into nothingness when I go to bed, I pop an edible. Grabbing a warm hoodie, my lighter and my keys, I lock my door behind me as I head upstairs. Popping in one earbud and scrolling for something to listen to, I walk up the stairs from my top floor apartment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;Watching a bunch of YouTube locksmithing videos had its benefits. A simple whim and an improvised rake got me on the roof of my building in the first few weeks here. My late schedule stops anyone from ever noticing me up there, so I hid a camping chair to use, and I usually go up to vibe to music, smoke, or both. While I'm allowed to smoke inside, I don't want visitors to deal with a bad smell and think I'm gross. (I'd have to actually have visitors first, though.)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;With one hand I grab the little jumble of bent paper clips hanging on my key ring and shove them in the door. A bit of motion on the pins and the lock turns, letting me onto the roof. The door slams behind me while I make my decision and select an album. Holding my bong and digging for my light, I hear something strange. Almost like someone quickly shuffling a bunch of poker chips across the roof. More metallic?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;Looking up, I see the strangest thing that I have ever seen in real life. At first, I’m pretty sure I’m seeing a big octopus. A bulbous ‘head’ seems to stare back, but it has too many limbs. There seem to be dozens, from long white strings to gray gripping appendages with soft orange lines running down them. Many are almost like jellyfish tendrils, a few more like squid or octopus limbs. Already alert, it raises itself higher, 4 feet or so tall, like it's an animal trying to intimidate me. It stands amongst a pile of strange little metal pieces that click and climb up its body. I watch as it's covered in strange semi-reflective segments, almost making it look like a big horrible crab or something. Cephalopod eyes dot its head at regular intervals. The ones facing in my direction stare right back at me as I watch it move slightly forward.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;For a few moments, we simply lock eyes and wonder what the other will do.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;I mutter to myself, “I'm not high enough for this to be a hallucination.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;Wayward Two-Seventeen is getting tired, two remain.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt; Simple report. Send it back to the field commander. A bit later, the transponder pings. Checking the response is a formality, the content is known and expected. Two more objects and today's calibration is over. Looking at the next object from above a window, this one sighs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;The automatic survey systems were pretty good, after calibration. Without that calibration, the system can have some trouble with objects of similar function but differing surface forms. This one scrolls through the generated diagrams for the strange object. Were the computer a bit better at large topologies, the risk of direct confirmation wouldn’t have been necessary, as it’s directly on top of a family home in a populous area. Still, one categorizes it: another signal receiver, as weird as it looks. A jumble of parallel and perpendicular metal tines, presumably to catch as much signal as possible, or something (one is not a comm systems expert). A simple selection and the computer system makes the connection. On to the next.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;The next location would be a minute or so away if the skyhook were authorized. Unfortunately it can't be authorized in middle density areas until the local survey is complete. This one takes a bit to directly navigate through the city. Even with active camouflage there’s some difficulty getting around without notice. The combination of the night cycle, and psyche of the population seems to work favorably here, despite all the lights.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-indent:36pt"&gt;&lt;span style="color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline"&gt;Several minutes later, and one reaches the destination, a small nature preserve, of sorts. The towering local plants provide some cover from the sky and the lights of the city. There is, however, a light